[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man charged with attempted murder over Stockport collision

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been charged with attempted murder after a 41-year-old was hit by a car in Stockport, Greater Manchester.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
A man was walking on High Street in Cheadle towards Ashfield Road when he was struck by a silver A-Class Mercedes at about 19:50 GMT on Boxing Day.
Greater Manchester Police said the injured man was in a serious but stable condition in hospital.
A 32-year-old man from Cheadle Hulme is due to appear at Stockport Magistrates Court later.
